defs.docs:
A pure rust replacement for the [miniz](https://github.com/richgel999/miniz)
 DEFLATE/zlib encoder/decoder.
 The plan for this crate is to be used as a back-end for the
 [flate2](https://github.com/alexcrichton/flate2-rs) crate and eventually remove the
 need to depend on a C library.

defs.name: deflate
defs.docs: This module contains functionality for compression.

defs.name: TDEFL_WRITE_ZLIB_HEADER

defs.docs: Should we compute the adler32 checksum.

defs.name: TDEFL_GREEDY_PARSING_FLAG
defs.docs:
Should we use greedy parsing (as opposed to lazy parsing where look ahead one or more
 bytes to check for better matches.)

defs.name: TDEFL_NONDETERMINISTIC_PARSING_FLAG
defs.docs:
Used in miniz to skip zero-initializing hash and dict. We don't do this here, so
 this flag is ignored.

defs.name: TDEFL_RLE_MATCHES
defs.docs: Only look for matches with a distance of 0.

defs.name: TDEFL_FILTER_MATCHES
defs.docs: Only use matches that are at least 6 bytes long.

defs.name: TDEFL_FORCE_ALL_STATIC_BLOCKS
defs.docs:
Force the compressor to only output static blocks. (Blocks using the default huffman codes
 specified in the deflate specification.)

defs.name: TDEFL_FORCE_ALL_RAW_BLOCKS
defs.docs: Force the compressor to only output raw/uncompressed blocks.

defs.name: Default
defs.docs: Don't use any of the special strategies.

defs.name: Filtered
defs.docs: Only use matches that are at least 5 bytes long.

defs.name: HuffmanOnly
defs.docs: Don't look for matches, only huffman encode the literals.

defs.name: RLE
defs.docs: Only look for matches with a distance of 1, i.e do run-length encoding only.

defs.name: Fixed
defs.docs:
Only use static/fixed blocks. (Blocks using the default huffman codes
 specified in the deflate specification.)

Compress as much as there is space for, and then return

defs.name: Full
defs.docs:
Same as sync, but reset the dictionary so that the following data does not depend
 on previous data.

defs.name: Finish

defs.docs: Don't do any compression, only output uncompressed blocks.

defs.name: BestSpeed
defs.docs: Fast compression. Uses a special compression routine that is optimized for speed.

defs.name: BestCompression
defs.docs: Slow/high compression. Do a lot of checks to try to find good matches.

defs.name: UberCompression
defs.docs: Even more checks, can be very slow.

defs.name: DefaultLevel
defs.docs: Default compromise between speed and compression.

defs.name: DefaultCompression
defs.docs: Use the default compression level.

defs.name: CompressionLevel
defs.value: CompressionLevel::{NoCompression, BestSpeed, BestCompression, UberCompression, DefaultLevel, DefaultCompression}
defs.docs:
How much processing the compressor should do to compress the data.
 `NoCompression` and `Bestspeed` have special meanings, the other levels determine the number
 of checks for matches in the hash chains and whether to use lazy or greedy parsing.

More input data was expected, but the caller indicated that there was more data, so the
 input stream is likely truncated.

defs.name: None
defs.docs:
Don't force any flushing.
 Used when more input data is expected.

defs.name: Partial
defs.docs:
Zlib partial flush.
 Currently treated as `Sync`.

defs.name: Sync
defs.docs:
Finish compressing the currently buffered data, and output an empty raw block.
 Has no use in decompression.

defs.name: Full
defs.docs:
Same as `Sync`, but resets the compression dictionary so that further compressed
 data does not depend on data compressed before the flush.
 Has no use in decompression.

defs.name: Finish
defs.docs: Attempt to flush the remaining data and end the stream.

defs.name: Block
defs.docs: Not implemented.
